Confusion Matrix of Logistic Regression by Crosstab¶

Cross tab is alternate of confusion matrix. Because we have more then 2 target classes thats why we use that. In diognal we have TP. On column except TP we have FP and on row except TP we have FN for particular class. And rest of the value is TN for particular class.

In [375]:
con_LR = confusion_matrix(test_y, y_pred_LR)
FP_LR = (con_LR.sum(axis=0) - np.diag(con_LR))
FN_LR = (con_LR.sum(axis=1) - np.diag(con_LR))
TP_LR = np.diag(con_LR)
TN_LR = con_LR.sum() - (FP_LR + FN_LR + TP_LR)
print(TP_LR, FN_LR, FP_LR, TN_LR)

Performance Measurement , Target Class: Summary¶

In [382]:
from sklearn import tree, metrics
from sklearn.preprocessing import label_binarize
from sklearn.multiclass import OneVsRestClassifier
from sklearn import preprocessing
def multiclass_roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred, average="macro"):
    lb = preprocessing.LabelBinarizer()
    lb.fit(y_test)
    y_test = lb.transform(y_test)
    y_pred = lb.transform(y_pred)
    return metrics.roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred, average=average)
